  "prompt": "Is Sadhguru a conman?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge up to October 2023, Sadhguru Jaggi Vasudev, commonly known as Sadhguru, is a well-known Indian yogi, mystic, and founder of the Isha Foundation. He has a significant following worldwide and is recognized for his teachings on spirituality, inner well-being, and social initiatives.\n\nHowever, like many public figures, Sadhguru has his share of supporters and critics. While many admire his work and consider him a genuine spiritual leader, others have raised concerns or criticisms regarding various aspects of his activities or the operations of his foundation. It's important to approach such claims critically and seek information from reputable and unbiased sources.\n\nAccusations labeling someone as a \"conman\" are serious and should be supported by credible evidence. As of the latest information available, there is no widespread, substantiated evidence to categorically label Sadhguru as a conman. If you have specific concerns or have encountered claims of this nature, I recommend reviewing reliable sources, such as reputable news outlets or official statements, and exercising critical judgment when evaluating such information.\n\nRemember to consider multiple perspectives and verify the credibility of sources when forming an opinion on public figures.",
